comment: Lemma for ~ ang180 . Show that the "revolution number" ` N ` is an integer, using ~ efeq1 to show that since the product of the three arguments ` A , 1 / ( 1 - A ) , ( A - 1 ) / A ` is ` -u 1 ` , the sum of the logarithms must be an integer multiple of ` 2 _pi _i ` away from ` _pi _i = log ( -u 1 ) ` . (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 23-Sep-2014.)
